<tr id="L345"><td><a href="#L345">345</a></td><td>PICARD:  Kevin does. He's the cause. At first I couldn't understand why your house survived the holocaust when the others hadn't. Then it occurred to me. It had been destroyed. That dwelling, where you served me tea, where you danced your waltzes, is a reproduction. Real to the touch but capable of being created, destroyed, and created. All on a whim.</td></tr>

<tr id="L346"><td><a href="#L346">346</a></td><td>RISHON:  You're joking with us, Captain. Can't you see this is hurting my husband?</td></tr>

